            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they evoked the meditations ..., they made disappear all the passions of the world of desire and of the world of form; [and] also according to the right rule they went away to the city of cessation and of Nirvāṇa. – </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Besides these ones [also did the following]: || in [the metre] (...) || "The Bodhisattvas [have] an unquenchable (abilit)y concerning virtues, [they have] hidden the [beings of the] five births in the vast hole of compassion. Thereupon,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they sti(mulate) the thought towards (all nob)le undertakings. From where would, in large scale, the prosperity for all beings come from?" 1 Thereupon, some of this kind</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">having lived a long time, having understood the constellations [and] the [astrological] moments; they established the Śāstras, beginning with the science of the year, grammar, [and] horoscope;</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>158</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">some of this kind established the Vedas. The gods equipped with a great power gave them approbation. Thereupon, these came to (reside) in an house as [their] refuge:</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5 #a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Zum zweiten Mal kamen sie in das Dorf zurück, bildeten [sich] Behausungen [und] ... [und] übten ebendort Sittlichkeit.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">For the second time they came back to the village, established housing [for themselves], [and] there [they] observed morality.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>405, 440</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they returned again to their village, they constructed houses [and] enclosures. Right there they observed [pious] observation, they recited the canonical Śāstras.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6 #b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>157</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">|| This race following the Kṣatriyas was called the Brahmanic [race]. – Besides, also: || in [the metre] A. || "Those that were at first ca(lled) thus [i.e. Brahmins], of this kind is the Brahmanic state [i.e. they define the Brahmanic state].</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">They intermingled with the society of householders. From the efforts of those surely emerges [lit. adheres] the knowledge: (together with a)rt there were (the thinking) [and] (the reflec)tion." 1 || Now these </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">rules were proclaimed under the king Mahāsaṃmata: [There are] Kṣatriyas, Brahmins, [and] Vaiśyas. – But this in which way? || in [the metre] Y. || "Without number, </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">greatly, here the bein(gs turn)ed towards a life of tranquillity. The gods from on high descended to earth into the company of men, in order to achieve well-being, the establishment</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">of (all) virtues, ... (prosperi)ty. These ones [= the gods] had not heard the ultimate name, namely death." 1 Meanwhile, the</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013a"/><citedRange>251</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">god king [Indra] established himself on the throne, he sent the first queen [being an] ornament to the king Mahāsaṃmata as [token of] remembrance; together he [Indra] made friendship with him. There(upon) ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
